subSubSection.paragraph:
Females (
Fig. 2
): Ground colour of body light brownish gray with dark marks, highly variable in size, number and shape. Sometimes one or two black spots on anterocentral portion of flank. Pectoral and ventral region hyaline. Opercular region ochre or pale greenish blue. Caudal peduncle with two vertically arranged black spots (sometimes coalescing into a eight-shaped spot) on posterior portion. Opercular region pale blue. Iris light yellow. Dark gray vertical band crossing the eye. Unpaired fins hyaline, with faint gray marks or bars, mainly on basal portion of dorsal and anal fins. Pectoral fins hyaline.
